&quot;Epic doesnt take a large guild and can easily be done by a part time player. Those saying otherwise are no thinking clearly. Phinny takes 1 grp (or less) with lvl 50ish gimp gear, PoF takes 2 groups with lvl 55ish low budget gear, VS is a sissy, maybe 3 grps of 50's, as long as you got the right classes folks chaining runes/heals and a MT that can hold agro. &quot;<br>
<br>
I would agree with you that it doesn't take a large guild to do but it is by no means easily done by a part time player in a small guild. I agree that phinny can be done with 1 group or less but, the &quot;average&quot; casual player in the &quot;average&quot; small guild of below 60th level isn't likely to do him in &quot;gimp gear&quot;. Make that about level 60 and I agree with you whole heartedly.<br>
<br>
I was in PoF around 55 in my &quot;low budget gear&quot;. 2 groups at that level with that power level are hardly gonna break in easily, even with beforehand knowledge. Again, make that average level 60 and I'd agree with you.<br>
<br>
VS may be a sissy to you but, to some he's still a pain in the ass. Finding him up is probably the hardest part, at least on my server. Sorry but, in a small guild, I don't just happen to have 3 groups waiting for 3 straight days to come take him out at a moment's notice. You're dreaming if you think most small guilds have that ability. Small guilds are small for a reason. Casual players are casual for a reason.<br>
<br>
&quot;So really, and tiny guild of part timers can do this. Just takes having friends that care about you. If your friends don't care enough to come help, I would suggest that they aint yer friends and to run out and get some new ones.&quot;<br>
<br>
I agree with the general idea of the post, just not the elitist &quot;everything is gimp cuz I can do it&quot; attitude used to express the idea. Wiz epic is alot easier now than when it was introduced. For most casuals in small guilds, though, it's really more a matter of finding those mobs up at the times when you actually have a force available to complete the encounter.<br>
<br>
Oh, and as a friend, I wouldn't expect or try to push my friends into doing any of these camps with me. Casual players in small guilds are usually busy during their limited play time. Asking those friends to spend all of their game time to continuously break Fear or camp VS on the off chance those mobs are actually up and not being engaged isn't really being much of a friend at all.<br>
<br>
